The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 27: All major airlines, including Air India and Jet Airways, have come up with special fares to attract domestic passengers during the monsoons. Air India is offering special fares from today up to September 15. But tickets at these rates have to be bought by July 3. Jet Airways and its low-cost arms have launched special Monsoon Magic prices.                            
	 Panaji, June 27: Union minister of petroleum and natural gas Murli Deora today said the government was closely monitoring global crude oil prices before deciding on a hike in the prices of petroleum products.                             
	 Mumbai, June 27: The countrys forex reserves rose $8 million to $263.65 billion for the week ended June 19 compared with $263.64 billion in the previous week. Foreign currency assets during the week jumped $10 million to $252.80 billion against $252.79 billion in the previous week, the RBI said.                                                                                                                           
